Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Place the steaks in a 9x13 inch baking dish and season with cumin and salt and pepper to taste. Arrange the pepper and onion over the meat and pour salsa over all, adding some water as needed to the bottom of the baking dish. Cover with foil. Bake at 375 degrees F (190 degrees C) for 30 to 40 minutes.